Note:
Runa Self-Hosting Build System
This replaces the Python bootstrap script once self-hosting is established
The goal: Runa builds Runa with no external dependencies
:End Note

Type BuildResult is:
    | Success with artifacts as Dictionary[String, String] and time_seconds as Float
    | Failure with error as String

Type BuildStep is:
    | CompileBootstrap 
    | CompileSelfHosting
    | CreateExecutable
    | VerifyBuild
    | CleanArtifacts

Process called "main" that takes args as List[String] returns Integer:
    Note: Main entry point for Runa build system
    Display "🚀 Runa Self-Hosting Build System"
    Display "Building Runa with Runa..."
    
    Let start_time be current_time_ms
    Let build_result be execute_build_pipeline
    Let end_time be current_time_ms
    
    Match build_result:
        When Success with artifacts as artifacts and time_seconds as time:
            Display "✅ Self-hosting build completed successfully!"
            Display "Build time: " joined with time joined with " seconds"
            Display "Artifacts created:"
            For each artifact_name in keys of artifacts:
                Let artifact_path be artifacts at key artifact_name
                Display "  " joined with artifact_name joined with ": " joined with artifact_path
            Return 0
        When Failure with error as error:
            Display "❌ Build failed: " joined with error
            Return 1

Process called "execute_build_pipeline" returns BuildResult:
    Note: Execute the complete self-hosting build pipeline
    Let artifacts be dictionary containing
    
    Note: Step 1: Compile self-hosting compiler
    Display "Step 1: Compiling Runa compiler from source..."
    Let compiler_result be compile_compiler_source
    
    Match compiler_result:
        When Failure with error as error:
            Return Failure with error as "Compiler compilation failed: " joined with error
        When Success with bytecode_path as bytecode_path:
            Set artifacts at key "compiler_bytecode" to bytecode_path
    
    Note: Step 2: Create executable wrapper
    Display "Step 2: Creating executable wrapper..."
    Let executable_result be create_executable_wrapper with bytecode_path as compiler_result.bytecode_path
    
    Match executable_result:
        When Failure with error as error:
            Return Failure with error as "Executable creation failed: " joined with error
        When Success with executable_path as executable_path:
            Set artifacts at key "executable" to executable_path
    
    Note: Step 3: Self-compilation verification
    Display "Step 3: Verifying self-compilation..."
    Let verification_result be verify_self_compilation with executable_path as executable_result.executable_path
    
    Match verification_result:
        When Failure with error as error:
            Return Failure with error as "Self-compilation verification failed: " joined with error
        When Success:
            Display "✅ Self-compilation verified!"
    
    Return Success with artifacts as artifacts and time_seconds as 0.0

Process called "compile_compiler_source" returns BuildResult:
    Note: Compile the Runa compiler from Runa source files
    Let source_dir be "src/compiler/"
    Let main_file be source_dir joined with "main.runa"
    Let output_file be "build/runa_compiler.bc"
    
    Note: Use external compiler to bootstrap (this is the transition point)
    Let compile_command be list containing "runac", "compile", main_file, "-o", output_file
    Let result be execute_system_command with command as compile_command
    
    If result.success:
        Return Success with bytecode_path as output_file
    Otherwise:
        Return Failure with error as result.error

Process called "create_executable_wrapper" that takes bytecode_path as String returns BuildResult:
    Note: Create shell script wrapper for the compiler bytecode
    Let executable_path be "build/runa"
    Let wrapper_content be create_wrapper_script with bytecode_path as bytecode_path
    
    Let write_result be write_file with path as executable_path and content as wrapper_content
    If write_result.success:
        Let chmod_result be make_executable with path as executable_path
        If chmod_result.success:
            Return Success with executable_path as executable_path
        Otherwise:
            Return Failure with error as "Failed to make executable: " joined with chmod_result.error
    Otherwise:
        Return Failure with error as "Failed to write wrapper: " joined with write_result.error

Process called "verify_self_compilation" that takes executable_path as String returns BuildResult:
    Note: Verify that the compiler can compile itself
    Let test_source be create_test_program
    Let test_file be "build/test_self_compilation.runa"
    Let test_output be "build/test_self_compilation.bc"
    
    Note: Write test program
    Let write_result be write_file with path as test_file and content as test_source
    If not write_result.success:
        Return Failure with error as "Failed to write test program: " joined with write_result.error
    
    Note: Compile with self-hosting compiler
    Let compile_command be list containing executable_path, "compile", test_file, "-o", test_output
    Let compile_result be execute_system_command with command as compile_command
    
    If not compile_result.success:
        Return Failure with error as "Self-compilation test failed: " joined with compile_result.error
    
    Note: Verify output exists
    If file_exists with path as test_output:
        Return Success
    Otherwise:
        Return Failure with error as "Test compilation produced no output"

Process called "create_wrapper_script" that takes bytecode_path as String returns String:
    Note: Create shell script that executes the compiler bytecode
    Return "#!/bin/bash
# Runa Self-Hosting Compiler
# Generated by build_system.runa

SCRIPT_DIR=\"$(cd \"$(dirname \"${BASH_SOURCE[0]}\")\" && pwd)\"
PROJECT_ROOT=\"$(dirname \"$SCRIPT_DIR\")\"
VM_EXECUTABLE=\"$PROJECT_ROOT/src/runtime/target/debug/runa-rt\"
COMPILER_BYTECODE=\"$SCRIPT_DIR/" joined with bytecode_path joined with "\"

# Check dependencies
if [ ! -f \"$VM_EXECUTABLE\" ]; then
    echo \"Error: Runa VM not found. Please build runtime: cd src/runtime && cargo build\"
    exit 1
fi

if [ ! -f \"$COMPILER_BYTECODE\" ]; then
    echo \"Error: Compiler bytecode not found: $COMPILER_BYTECODE\"
    exit 1
fi

# Execute self-hosting compiler
exec \"$VM_EXECUTABLE\" \"$COMPILER_BYTECODE\" \"$@\"
"

Process called "create_test_program" returns String:
    Note: Create simple test program for self-compilation verification
    Return "Note: Self-compilation test program
Let message be \"Self-hosting compilation successful!\"
Display message

Process called \"test_function\" that takes input as String returns String:
    Return \"Test result: \" joined with input

Let result be test_function with input as \"working\"
Display result
"

Note: System interface functions (to be implemented with FFI)
Process called "execute_system_command" that takes command as List[String] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Execute system command and return result
    Note: This would use FFI to call system commands
    Return dictionary containing:
        "success" as true
        "output" as ""
        "error" as ""

Process called "write_file" that takes path as String and content as String returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Write content to file
    Note: This would use FFI for file I/O
    Return dictionary containing:
        "success" as true
        "error" as ""

Process called "make_executable" that takes path as String returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Make file executable (chmod +x)
    Note: This would use FFI for filesystem operations
    Return dictionary containing:
        "success" as true
        "error" as ""

Process called "file_exists" that takes path as String returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if file exists
    Note: This would use FFI for filesystem operations
    Return true

Process called "current_time_ms" returns Integer:
    Note: Get current time in milliseconds
    Note: This would use FFI for system time
    Return 0